                <pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">kluunʔ</pron>
                <pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">kuo̝n</pron>
            </form>
            <def>Gǔn 袞, according to Han sources, refers to the ceremonial dress of the ruler embroidered with dragon design. [ZGYI 1996: 131]. In the Western Zhou and Chunqiu period, the term refers to the embroidered ritual dress. [XIANG 1997: 213 - 214; JWCYZD 1992: 804]
</def>
